</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1156,142,203]" box="[160,1156,178,203]" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">
<collectingCountry box="[160,207,178,203]" name="Italy" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Italy</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[262,342,178,203]" name="Croatia" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Korshunova T &amp; Malmberg K &amp; Prkic J &amp; Petani A &amp; Fletcher K &amp; Lundin K &amp; Martynov A" box="[353,608,178,203]" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" pagination="15 - 50" refId="ref20167" refString="Korshunova T, Malmberg K, Prkic J, Petani A, Fletcher K, Lundin K, Martynov A. 2020. Fine-scale species delimitation: speciation in process and periodic patterns in nudibranch diversity. ZooKeys. 917: 15 - 50. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 917.47444." type="journal article" year="2020">Korshunova et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[626,701,178,203]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">France</collectingCountry>
(this study); 
<collectingCountry box="[842,907,178,203]" name="Spain" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Spain</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[916,1021,178,203]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
(this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="284" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1157,262,600]" box="[160,262,262,288]" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,262,288]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1157,262,600]" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">
This species was recently described, but up to now it was considered a morphotype of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alder and Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[194,409,332,357]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eubranchidae" genus="Eubranchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="farrani">
<emphasis box="[194,409,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Eubranchus farrani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now 
<taxonomicName authority="(Alder and Hancock 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Alder and Hancock" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[487,1017,332,357]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eubranchidae" genus="Amphorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="farrani">
<emphasis box="[487,696,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Amphorina farrani</emphasis>
(Alder and Hancock 1845)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korshunova, Malmberg, Prkic, Petani, Fletcher, Lundin, Martynov" authorityYear="2020" class="Gastropoda" family="Eubranchidae" genus="Amphorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="andra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Amphorina andra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is variable in body colour, from completely white or orange to a white with black spots and orange circles on the dorsum. Specimens found at deeper depths were typically small, whereas specimens found at very shallow depths, mostly in caves, were larger and found on hydrozoan colonies of the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peron &amp; Lesueur" authorityYear="1810" box="[1024,1097,471,496]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Campanulariidae" genus="Obelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1024,1097,471,496]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Obelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[160,285,506,531]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertularellidae" genus="Sertularella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,285,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Sertularella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, among others. Populations observed in 
<collectingCountry box="[782,863,506,531]" name="Croatia" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Croatia</collectingCountry>
were in shallow waters, between 0 and 
<quantity box="[344,409,540,565]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" unit="m" value="0.5">0.5 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Korshunova T &amp; Malmberg K &amp; Prkic J &amp; Petani A &amp; Fletcher K &amp; Lundin K &amp; Martynov A" box="[424,692,540,565]" pageId="19" pageNumber="284" pagination="15 - 50" refId="ref20167" refString="Korshunova T, Malmberg K, Prkic J, Petani A, Fletcher K, Lundin K, Martynov A. 2020. Fine-scale species delimitation: speciation in process and periodic patterns in nudibranch diversity. ZooKeys. 917: 15 - 50. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 917.47444." type="journal article" year="2020">Korshunova et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
), as was the population studied in Sant Feliu, 
<collectingRegion box="[231,338,575,600]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[355,424,575,600]" name="Spain" pageId="19" pageNumber="284">Spain</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
